I want to add a hidden developer/pro mode activation feature to this Android app. The mechanism should work exactly like this implementation:

A tap sequence on two separate UI elements activates a key-entry dialog: 7 taps on one element within 4 seconds, then 2 taps on a second element within 4 seconds of the 7th tap
When the sequence is detected, show an AlertDialog with an OutlinedTextField for the user to paste a key
The key is verified by computing its SHA-256 hash and comparing to a stored constant: b2280f06c2a7401da8dc71f858c1d513d491c0b3ad80823f6e8cb8d2de7fc3ea
If the hash matches, store dev_mode_active = true in EncryptedSharedPreferences and grant Pro/developer status
A long-press (5+ seconds) on the same first element deactivates developer mode
Developer mode persists across app restarts until explicitly deactivated
The same key hash is used across multiple apps by the same developer. Implement this using the same pattern — EncryptedSharedPreferences, SHA-256 comparison, no network calls.

